        "timestamp": 1717976741
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For me I <code>git clone</code>'ed the entire source code of Mathlib locally, then use <code>grep</code> or VSCode's \"search in project\" feature + guessing the theorem name to find theorems.</p>\n<p>Here are the results. It seems the result doesn't exist, but it should be easy to prove. I assume you mean <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>⊗</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>⊗</mo><mi>C</mi><mtext>  </mtext><mo>⟹</mo><mtext>  </mtext><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A \\otimes B = A \\otimes C \\implies B = C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7073em;vertical-align:-0.024em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⟹</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span> if any element of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span></span></span> is invertible?</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/-cO-zqRYsbg_8vufXCrX8EM2/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/-cO-zqRYsbg_8vufXCrX8EM2/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/3121/-cO-zqRYsbg_8vufXCrX8EM2/image.png\"></a></div>",
